  Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Alice Holcombe was born in 1485, in Devon, England, United Kingdom. She married Sir Knight William Perry in 1487, in Devon, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1520, in her hometown, at the age of 35."},"et":{"1485–1520":"1485–1520","1464–1565":"1464–1565","1500–1580":"1500–1580","1500":"1500","1565":"1565","1520":"1520","1464":"1464","1485":"1485","Abt. 1487":"1487","1580":"1580","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England"," Devon, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1485–1520":"1485–1520","1464–1565":"1464–1565","1500–1580":"1500–1580","1500":"1500","1565":"1565","1520":"1520","1464":"1464","1485":"1485","Abt. 1487":"1487","1580":"1580","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England"," Devon, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Devon, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1485–1520":"1485–1520","1464–1565":"1464–1565","1500–1580":"1500–1580","1500":"1500","1565":"1565","1520":"1520","1464":"1464","1485":"1485","Abt. 1487":"1487","1580":"1580","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Angleterre"," Devon, England":"Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Devon, England":"Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lady Alic